            <div class="bioText">
                <p>Guitarist/composer Karl Grossman is available for session work, as producer and arranger, or as a composer. He takes influence from several styles and diciplines in his approach to musical arts. Playing music since early years starting on trumpet, Karl continues to push the envelope on repetoire and improvisational technique with his guitar. He is also able to satisfy an ever growing client list of professional musicians. Karl manages the Music Focus facility in Hermosa Beach, California.
                        "Jazz was my first love. I lived and breathed the jazz guitar tone. But I was always amused and intrigued by blues and distorted rock guitar. I'll always regret that I didn't accept and get into the finger style and classical guitar styles much earlier. But I love all styles of music the power of rock, the minimalism of new wave, the bravura of metal, soul of blues, harmonic challenge of classical and the ambiguousness and improvisational halo of jazz. Learning all you can about the different styles is the best way to grow. Every song I learn shows me or re-confirms some aspect of music theory or physical guitar ability."</p>
                <p>Karl's foray into Gypsy Rumba style nylon guitar arts has been an amazing voyage. Karl has written over 90 beautiful, challenging original pieces from soothing to broiling! Concert appearances at NAMM, San Juan Capistrano, Paradise CA, and numerous solo performances for events and private functions have furthur broadened his range. "I feel blessed to have found a really powerful style. The right hand coordination with the chords and melody, not to mention bass lines, all combine to make this style a truly awesome challenge." Karl has created a "YouTube" platform under his "guitarist karl grossman" name... Just search - guitarist karl grossman - in YouTube... Happy listening!</p>
            </div>
