                    <div class="bioText">
                        <p>Karl is an active guitar instructor and has taught literally hundreds of students in the South Bay. Former students are now in the bands Easter, Centerfold, and Phantom Blue. (Add your name to Karl's list if you want! Students)<br>
                                Though Karl attended UCSB, UCLA, and Dominguez Hills Universities, it was the work at El Camino with music theory professor Wallace Bower that bonded a fine understanding of music theory with ear training, composition, piano skills and advanced theory concepts...<br>
                                "Those years studying music theory were filled with revelations. I realized and was encouraged to explore the connection between emotional nature of sound and the technical names for it. I always encourage my students to seek their own definitions for actual sounds. Minor triads can be cold, dark, purple, sad, or scary while major triads can be bright, sunny, yellow, happy, hot or glowing. Theoretical musical definitions do not give any insight on what emotional response these musical elements may trigger in someone. But once there is a connection between the two, the bond is made!"
                                Karl offers a combination of talents to his students. One is to teach patiently and cohesively, and the other is to inspire students with the joy and humor of making good music.<br>
                                <span>Thanks for jammin'!</span><br>
                                BTW, this sketch was made in Pasadena at a club Karl played at in the late 80's. 'Thank you' to the unknown artist!</p>
                        
